<a href="http://www.mutedfaith.com/quiz/q3.htm" target="new"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/14/02 7:47:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1398.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: &lt;snicker&gt;</span><hr size=1> Were Monks overpowered?  Yeah, SOME of them were.  I don't think this was the best way to change monks though.  The problem wasn't necessarily monk mitigation, although it is more than a bit absurd that some fool in silk can mitigate a sword thrust as well as someone encased in metal.  The problem was the number of all/all 0.1 weight uber ac items.  That's where I think the adjustment needed to be made, some sort of weight penalties there.  The changes will probably have no appreciable effect on the uber monks but could really screw the non-ubers who don't have access to all the all/all gear.<br>
<br>
Outside of the small, vocal, brainless minority, I don't think warriors are all that thrilled about monks being nerfed.  If the monk community wants to view it that way, it's their business, but warriors don't write the game's code...<br>
